gio Agamben, Catherine Malabou, François Laruelle, Peter Sloterdijk, and Gilles Deleuze yet rejuvenate scholarship in continental philosophy, critical race theory, the new materialisms, speculative realism, and nonphilosophy. They think beyond the sovereign force of the one to initiate a radical politics "after" God.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aPolitical theology. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh1 aBlanton, Ward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrockett, Clayton, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aCrockett, Clayton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavis, Creston, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavis, Creston.1 aKeller, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeller, Catherine.1 aRobbins, Jeffrey W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobbins, Jeffrey, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRollins, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRollins, Peter.1 aVahanian, Noëlle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311063857840uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/blan1762240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231541732423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231541732.jpg  a978-3-11-063857-8  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles